WEBVTT

00:00:00.040 --> 00:00:14.740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

00:00:36.440 --> 00:00:39.040
We're from the Criminal Investigation Brigade. Please step out and open your trunk

00:00:39.040 --> 00:00:40.100
for an inspection.

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:15.760
Master.

00:01:16.280 --> 00:01:17.080
Brother Chen.

00:01:17.600 --> 00:01:19.200
Just as I thought, it's here.

00:01:26.160 --> 00:01:26.720
How is it?

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:28.000
Oh.

00:01:28.560 --> 00:01:30.240
Based on the previous body assembly

00:01:30.240 --> 00:01:31.680
and this skull examination,

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:32.600
we can basically confirm

00:01:32.600 --> 00:01:33.840
that Wang Xichuan's fatal wound

00:01:33.840 --> 00:01:36.900
was caused by blunt force trauma to the back of the head.

00:01:37.400 --> 00:01:38.259
A blunt weapon?

00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:40.280
Can you determine what kind of blunt weapon?

00:01:40.280 --> 00:01:41.440
We can't be sure yet.

00:01:41.960 --> 00:01:44.000
However, there is intracranial bruising.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:46.400
Based on the depth of the skull depression,

00:01:46.479 --> 00:01:48.440
it should be something like a brick.

00:01:48.440 --> 00:01:49.560
Oh, but not that big.

00:01:49.560 --> 00:01:50.320
A brick?

00:01:50.479 --> 00:01:50.810
Yeah.

00:01:50.880 --> 00:01:51.210
Here.

00:01:52.840 --> 00:01:54.900
What's the depth of this depression?

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:56.660
About five millimeters deep.

00:02:00.400 --> 00:02:03.400
The murder weapon should still be at the Wang's house.

00:02:06.360 --> 00:02:07.760
We've searched everywhere in here.

00:02:07.760 --> 00:02:09.289
We almost tore the roof off.

00:02:09.360 --> 00:02:09.960
The murder weapon

00:02:09.960 --> 00:02:10.960
is not in the room.

00:02:11.480 --> 00:02:12.160
If it is,

00:02:12.160 --> 00:02:14.120
it should be somewhere outside.

00:02:15.240 --> 00:02:15.640
Hey.

00:02:16.160 --> 00:02:17.490
Are you listening to me?

00:03:05.400 --> 00:03:06.840
You've been looking for a long time.

00:03:06.840 --> 00:03:08.080
Any new discoveries?

00:03:11.480 --> 00:03:12.810
What are you looking at?

00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:24.850
There should have been a brass paperweight here.

00:03:27.960 --> 00:03:29.920
Do you really think this brass paperweight

00:03:29.920 --> 00:03:30.720
is right here?

00:03:31.800 --> 00:03:34.360
Yang Xiaomei and Lin Xiaoai were locked up here for a long time.

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:35.840
If she were to hide something,

00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:38.760
she would definitely hide it in the more familiar cellar.

00:03:38.760 --> 00:03:39.240
Master.

00:03:39.240 --> 00:03:40.000
I found it.

00:03:57.240 --> 00:03:58.240
Officers.

00:03:59.120 --> 00:04:01.380
I've already told you everything I know.

00:04:01.520 --> 00:04:03.120
What else do you want to know?

00:04:15.360 --> 00:04:17.320
We have found Wang Xichuan's head.

00:04:17.959 --> 00:04:19.160
According to the forensic examination,

00:04:19.160 --> 00:04:20.959
the fatal wound is on the back of his head.

00:04:20.959 --> 00:04:21.440
And this

00:04:21.800 --> 00:04:23.000
is the murder weapon.

00:04:25.920 --> 00:04:27.840
Besides Wang Xichuan's,

00:04:28.320 --> 00:04:30.380
there is a partial fingerprint on it.

00:04:30.680 --> 00:04:31.740
After comparison,

00:04:32.200 --> 00:04:32.860
it's yours.

00:04:41.520 --> 00:04:42.159
Now,

00:04:42.640 --> 00:04:44.240
the evidence is conclusive.

00:05:04.120 --> 00:05:05.200
The one in the cellar

00:05:05.200 --> 00:05:06.530
is my daughter-in-law.

00:05:07.040 --> 00:05:08.240
She was disobedient,

00:05:08.400 --> 00:05:09.560
so she was locked up.

00:05:12.040 --> 00:05:12.500
Then...

00:05:12.720 --> 00:05:14.600
The heads in the wine jars

00:05:16.040 --> 00:05:17.120
are all real.

00:05:19.840 --> 00:05:21.680
If you disobey too,

00:05:22.400 --> 00:05:23.440
I'll put your head

00:05:25.560 --> 00:05:27.280
in a wine jar.

00:05:33.000 --> 00:05:34.800
I'll obey. I'll obey.

00:05:35.159 --> 00:05:36.520
I'll do whatever you say.

00:05:36.520 --> 00:05:38.800
I'll obey. I won't run away. I'll obey.

00:05:43.760 --> 00:05:44.400
Then

00:05:44.840 --> 00:05:46.159
tonight,

00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:48.610
you'll keep me company.

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:50.520
Ah!

00:05:51.280 --> 00:05:51.680
Mhm.

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:04.690
Let's go.

00:06:20.960 --> 00:06:21.690
Come with me.

00:06:37.920 --> 00:06:38.840
He's drunk.

00:06:41.360 --> 00:06:42.960
I wanted to kill him just now,

00:06:43.240 --> 00:06:46.560
but I thought it was more important to go down and save you first.

00:06:46.560 --> 00:06:47.240
Me too.

00:06:48.520 --> 00:06:50.600
I wanted to kill him every day.

00:06:50.960 --> 00:06:52.800
I wish I could hack him to pieces.

00:06:53.520 --> 00:06:54.680
But I was kept by them,

00:06:54.680 --> 00:06:55.810
locked up every day.

00:06:56.040 --> 00:06:57.159
I had no chance.

00:06:58.040 --> 00:06:59.040
I was also afraid.

00:07:00.400 --> 00:07:01.040
Now,

00:07:01.640 --> 00:07:04.500
isn't this a great opportunity right in front of us?

00:07:06.200 --> 00:07:06.840
But

00:07:07.280 --> 00:07:08.340
if we kill someone,

00:07:09.560 --> 00:07:11.690
the police will find out very quickly.

00:07:13.880 --> 00:07:14.610
I have a plan.

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:16.680
We can frame Wang Mingming,

00:07:16.680 --> 00:07:17.840
and we can frame Yang Zhigang too,

00:07:17.840 --> 00:07:19.770
and let the police arrest them all.

00:07:24.400 --> 00:07:25.080
Xiaomei.

00:07:26.440 --> 00:07:28.970
You've been tortured by them for three years.

00:07:29.320 --> 00:07:31.360
More than a thousand days and nights.

00:07:31.360 --> 00:07:33.220
Are you willing to just walk away?

00:07:34.159 --> 00:07:35.690
Don't you want to kill them?

00:07:36.320 --> 00:07:36.640
Ah.

00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:48.720
I wanted to kill him just now.

00:07:48.720 --> 00:07:50.780
I wanted to kill him with my own hands.

00:07:51.560 --> 00:07:53.840
But I was afraid I couldn't find the right spot,

00:07:53.840 --> 00:07:55.700
and it would be bad if I woke him up.

00:07:56.920 --> 00:07:58.880
Didn't you work at the meat processing plant?

00:07:58.880 --> 00:08:00.240
You must be better at this than me.

00:08:00.240 --> 00:08:00.960
You kill him.

00:08:00.960 --> 00:08:02.220
I'll handle the scene,

00:08:02.440 --> 00:08:03.840
and frame Wang Mingming.

00:08:59.840 --> 00:09:00.370
Xiaomei.

00:09:00.960 --> 00:09:01.760
You stay here.

00:09:02.160 --> 00:09:03.960
I'll go to Yang Zhigang's place.

00:09:05.920 --> 00:09:07.560
We'll both pretend to be victims,

00:09:07.560 --> 00:09:09.490
so the police won't think we did it.

00:09:09.640 --> 00:09:10.240
Then,

00:09:10.440 --> 00:09:11.900
what about the body parts?

00:09:12.360 --> 00:09:14.240
You're tired enough from dismembering the body.

00:09:14.240 --> 00:09:15.700
I'll take care of the rest.

00:09:16.040 --> 00:09:19.040
I'll hide the head in Yang Zhigang's slaughterhouse.

00:09:19.240 --> 00:09:21.680
Then we'll frame Yang Zhigang.

00:09:22.560 --> 00:09:23.800
Right.

00:09:24.800 --> 00:09:25.600
You stay here.

00:10:22.040 --> 00:10:22.570
Brother.

00:10:22.880 --> 00:10:24.160
Brother.

00:10:24.800 --> 00:10:25.360
Brother.

00:10:26.360 --> 00:10:27.090
What's wrong

00:10:27.240 --> 00:10:28.240
with you, sister?

00:10:31.880 --> 00:10:32.410
Found it.

00:10:41.080 --> 00:10:42.140
Why did you do this?

00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:44.200
Because I hate.

00:10:44.680 --> 00:10:45.640
I hate Wang Xichuan.

00:10:45.640 --> 00:10:46.320
I hate Wang Mingming.

00:10:46.320 --> 00:10:47.720
I hate Yang Xiaomei.

00:10:48.520 --> 00:10:51.240
If Yang Xiaomei hadn't insisted on taking me to get my fortune told back then,

00:10:51.240 --> 00:10:53.970
none of what happened later would have occurred.

00:10:54.480 --> 00:10:55.210
At that time,

00:10:56.040 --> 00:10:59.160
I was almost tortured to death by them.

00:11:00.280 --> 00:11:02.080
Fortunately, I was lucky enough

00:11:02.160 --> 00:11:03.080
to crawl out of

00:11:03.080 --> 00:11:04.160
the crop field

00:11:04.720 --> 00:11:06.850
and be saved by a kind-hearted person.

00:11:08.280 --> 00:11:10.010
Why didn't you call the police?

00:11:14.360 --> 00:11:15.760
I thought about calling the police.

00:11:15.760 --> 00:11:17.520
Have you ever thought about us women?

00:11:17.520 --> 00:11:17.800
Huh?

00:11:17.800 --> 00:11:19.730
Once these things are made public,

00:11:19.920 --> 00:11:21.440
our lives are over.

00:11:21.440 --> 00:11:22.240
Over.

00:11:23.320 --> 00:11:24.320
Your life?

00:11:24.720 --> 00:11:25.360
Do you know

00:11:25.360 --> 00:11:27.690
that two other girls were killed in there?

00:11:28.080 --> 00:11:29.360
Wang Xichuan cut off their heads

00:11:29.360 --> 00:11:30.490
and put them in jars.

00:11:30.800 --> 00:11:32.480
The bodies were buried in the crop field.

00:11:32.480 --> 00:11:33.800
Your life is a life.

00:11:34.360 --> 00:11:36.320
What about the lives of those two girls?

00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:37.380
Are they not lives?

00:11:38.960 --> 00:11:40.960
Did you start planning your revenge

00:11:41.040 --> 00:11:42.280
from that moment?

00:11:46.200 --> 00:11:48.400
Although I was lucky enough to survive,

00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:50.760
my life was worse than death every day.

00:11:50.920 --> 00:11:52.360
I wanted to die every day.

00:11:52.360 --> 00:11:54.040
I had nightmares every day.

00:11:54.120 --> 00:11:55.440
If I wasn't in the crop field,

00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:56.840
I was in the cellar.

00:11:57.040 --> 00:11:57.840
I was going crazy.

00:11:57.840 --> 00:11:59.160
I wanted to die so badly.

00:11:59.160 --> 00:12:02.020
I really wanted to commit suicide every single day.

00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:08.130
I was already standing on the rooftop.

00:12:09.600 --> 00:12:10.920
But I received a call.

00:12:20.440 --> 00:12:22.570
You are not the one who deserves to die.

00:12:23.360 --> 00:12:24.820
I can help you get revenge.

00:12:28.600 --> 00:12:30.120
Did he tell you who he was?

00:12:34.160 --> 00:12:34.720
No.

00:12:35.720 --> 00:12:36.980
From beginning to end,

00:12:37.640 --> 00:12:39.040
he used a virtual number.

00:12:40.160 --> 00:12:41.220
Was that the person

00:12:42.040 --> 00:12:43.440
who helped you plan this?

00:12:46.320 --> 00:12:48.360
What about the writing on the cellar wall?

00:12:48.360 --> 00:12:49.820
Did he tell you to write it?

00:13:04.640 --> 00:13:05.700
What did you write?

00:13:09.160 --> 00:13:10.760
It means 'sisters' in Nüshu.

00:13:11.960 --> 00:13:12.520
Xiaomei.

00:13:14.120 --> 00:13:16.250
I have always treated you as my sister.

00:13:16.360 --> 00:13:17.760
For the past three years,

00:13:18.160 --> 00:13:20.240
whenever I think of you still being here,

00:13:20.240 --> 00:13:21.240
I can't eat

00:13:21.240 --> 00:13:22.160
or sleep.

00:13:23.640 --> 00:13:24.800
I must save you.

00:13:39.960 --> 00:13:41.820
That mysterious person used you,

00:13:41.920 --> 00:13:43.480
and you used Yang Xiaomei.

00:13:44.160 --> 00:13:46.690
Yang Xiaomei still thinks you came to save her

00:13:47.080 --> 00:13:49.410
and that she killed Wang Xichuan herself.

00:13:52.920 --> 00:13:53.880
She owes me this.

00:13:55.080 --> 00:13:57.880
If you want to blame someone, blame her stupidity.

00:13:58.440 --> 00:13:59.400
I hate Wang Xichuan.

00:13:59.400 --> 00:14:00.160
I hate Wang Mingming.

00:14:00.160 --> 00:14:01.560
I hate Yang Xiaomei.

00:14:03.560 --> 00:14:06.560
If Yang Xiaomei hadn't insisted on dragging me to get my fortune told back then,

00:14:06.560 --> 00:14:09.290
none of what happened later would have occurred.

00:14:09.520 --> 00:14:11.380
That mysterious person used you.

00:14:11.440 --> 00:14:12.920
And you used Yang Xiaomei.

00:14:13.640 --> 00:14:16.600
Even now, Yang Xiaomei still thinks you came to save her,

00:14:16.600 --> 00:14:19.060
and thinks she killed Wang Xichuan herself.

00:14:19.920 --> 00:14:20.850
She owes me this.

00:14:22.120 --> 00:14:24.920
If you want to blame someone, blame her stupidity.

00:14:27.360 --> 00:14:28.200
I thought...

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:30.040
I thought she...

00:14:30.320 --> 00:14:31.080
You thought

00:14:31.360 --> 00:14:32.690
she was here to save you.

00:14:33.640 --> 00:14:34.720
If she wanted to save you,

00:14:34.720 --> 00:14:36.440
she would have come three years ago.

00:14:36.440 --> 00:14:38.040
She wouldn't wait until now.

00:14:38.520 --> 00:14:40.320
She has been using you all along.

00:15:27.920 --> 00:15:29.480
Brooding alone here again?

00:15:31.560 --> 00:15:33.440
Your talent for investigation, kid,

00:15:33.440 --> 00:15:35.240
is indeed a bit better than mine.

00:15:36.800 --> 00:15:40.060
But you were the one who finally found Wang Xichuan's head.

00:15:40.120 --> 00:15:41.520
Experience always wins.

00:15:41.640 --> 00:15:42.970
Who are you calling old?

00:15:43.000 --> 00:15:44.530
I'm still a spring chicken.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:46.040
Give me a break.

00:15:46.040 --> 00:15:47.120
Hahaha.

00:15:48.520 --> 00:15:49.000
Ah.

00:15:49.120 --> 00:15:50.240
I went over

00:15:50.520 --> 00:15:52.450
the old Scavenger case file again.

00:15:52.920 --> 00:15:54.240
I realized you found

00:15:54.560 --> 00:15:55.560
a lot of key clues.

00:15:56.920 --> 00:15:57.560
Oh.

00:15:57.880 --> 00:16:00.410
A true hero doesn't boast about past glories.

00:16:02.720 --> 00:16:04.450
About what happened back then,

00:16:05.160 --> 00:16:06.160
I don't blame you.

00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:07.860
Even though I punched you,

00:16:08.600 --> 00:16:09.660
I never blamed you.

00:16:11.240 --> 00:16:12.770
I believe you did your best.

00:16:14.760 --> 00:16:15.440
Is that it?

00:16:17.160 --> 00:16:18.720
Then I took that punch for nothing.

00:16:18.720 --> 00:16:21.050
You just didn't like me back then, did you?

00:16:23.240 --> 00:16:23.720
Yes.

00:16:24.480 --> 00:16:25.880
I was too narrow-minded.

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:29.320
Not every police officer

00:16:29.320 --> 00:16:30.520
has to be like my dad.

00:16:31.760 --> 00:16:34.290
Everyone has their own way of handling cases.

00:16:35.480 --> 00:16:36.040
Also,

00:16:37.040 --> 00:16:39.170
thank you for taking that knife for me.

00:16:40.000 --> 00:16:40.930
What did you say?

00:16:44.200 --> 00:16:44.960
Thank you

00:16:45.560 --> 00:16:47.160
for taking that knife for me.

00:16:49.360 --> 00:16:50.760
When I was young,

00:16:51.040 --> 00:16:52.100
I was reckless too.

00:16:52.600 --> 00:16:53.400
Fortunately,

00:16:53.640 --> 00:16:55.500
Captain Qiu always protected me.

00:16:59.560 --> 00:17:02.690
It's been a long time since anyone mentioned my dad to me.

00:17:03.320 --> 00:17:05.780
Even Aunt Rong would deliberately avoid it.

00:17:07.760 --> 00:17:08.480
Actually,

00:17:10.760 --> 00:17:12.760
I really want to hear about his past.

00:17:15.359 --> 00:17:16.079
Your dad,

00:17:19.000 --> 00:17:20.660
he liked watching the sunrise

00:17:21.359 --> 00:17:22.160
and sunset.

00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:25.490
He said seeing the sunlight

00:17:26.359 --> 00:17:27.480
gave him hope.

00:17:46.200 --> 00:17:46.760
Coming.

00:17:50.840 --> 00:17:51.440
Aunt Rong.

00:17:51.480 --> 00:17:52.210
You're here.

00:17:52.400 --> 00:17:52.760
Here.

00:17:58.160 --> 00:17:59.120
The case is solved.

00:17:59.120 --> 00:18:00.400
Let's celebrate.

00:18:01.720 --> 00:18:03.180
It's even a birthday cake.

00:18:04.040 --> 00:18:05.700
You've lost weight recently.

00:18:05.800 --> 00:18:08.060
I bought you something high in calories.

00:18:10.080 --> 00:18:10.440
Hey.

00:18:10.920 --> 00:18:12.920
Why did you open the curtains today?

00:18:14.320 --> 00:18:14.680
Ah.

00:18:15.440 --> 00:18:16.640
I just feel like

00:18:17.040 --> 00:18:18.200
getting some sun occasionally

00:18:18.200 --> 00:18:19.000
is quite nice.

00:18:19.760 --> 00:18:20.890
That's more like it.

00:18:22.240 --> 00:18:22.840
Aunt Rong,

00:18:23.280 --> 00:18:24.340
there's a question

00:18:24.520 --> 00:18:26.080
I've always wanted to ask you.

00:18:26.080 --> 00:18:26.610
Go ahead.

00:18:29.320 --> 00:18:32.580
Did you see Gu Yuming kill the Scavenger with your own eyes?

00:18:33.720 --> 00:18:35.050
I saw it with my own eyes.

00:18:35.320 --> 00:18:36.580
What about his motive?

00:18:37.120 --> 00:18:37.760
Alright.

00:18:38.120 --> 00:18:40.200
Don't think about the case during your break.

00:18:40.200 --> 00:18:41.060
Have some cake.

00:18:41.960 --> 00:18:42.480
Let me do it.